Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly grease a 13x9-inch baking dish. Mix potatoes, sour cream, cheese cubes, and cream of mushroom soup in a bowl; spread into prepared baking dish. Mix corn flakes cereal and butter in a bowl spread over the potato mixture. Bake in preheated oven until hot and bubbling, about 1 hour.